HitecAstro DC Focuser INDI driver install

Install your OS "build essentials" (gcc, binutils, etc).

Ensure you have followed the instructions to install INDI library following 
their instructions nd additionally add libindi-dev installation. Alternatively
clone from Githun the INDI project and follow it's build instructions.

https://github.com/indilib/indi

If you cannot build INDI Core you won't be able to build this driver.

Then...

1) git clone https://github.com/A-j-K/hitecastrodcfocuser.git
2) mkdir -p ~/hitecastrodcfocuser/build
3) cd ~/hitecastrodcfocuser/build
4) cmake ..
5) make
6) sudo make install

